properties.name: SafeCo Field
properties.description: Posted by GlynnjaminLiving in Tacoma for so many years, I saw plenty of games at SafeCo. This is one of the most beautiful, best designed ballparks in the country. The roof acts like an umbrella for the rain but you still feel like you are outside. The seats are great and the food is BY FAR the best in the Majors. My favorite moments at the Safe: ~Watching Cal Ripken Jr play his last game in Seattle on September 10th, 2001 with my mother, just before she flew out, narrowly missing the 9/11 no-fly span. ~Watching Ichiro rack up 262 hits in one season. ~Watching Edgar Martinez play his last game. ~Seeing Bret Boone play his last game. ~Watching the Mariners win 116 games and then lose to the Yankees. ~Flying in from Phoenix (after watching the Dbax beat the Cardinals in Game 5 of the NLDS) to watch the M\'s beat the Indians in Game 5 of the ALDS.
